correctness.rationale: The extraction conflates multiple experimental variants and contains numerous factual and schema errors. Key issues: (1) Process mixing: aldSystem.aldMethod lists ZnO by both PEALD and TALD and reactantSelection.coReactant includes both O2 and H2O for ZnO, while the supercycle (3/3/2) and most parameters correspond to the full-PEALD PE(1/1/1) sample. Separate PE(1/1/1) (PEALD for all three oxides) from T(1/1/1) (TALD only for ZnO) into distinct processes; do not mix methods within one process. (2) Pressure unit/value mismatch: article reports P_t in Pa (In: 10 Pa; Ga, Zn: 20 Pa; TALD-ZnO: 9 Pa). The JSON reports 20 MilliM_HG (mmHg), which is off by orders of magnitude; if schema requires MilliM_HG, convert 20 Pa ≈ 0.15 mmHg and note per-subcycle differences. (3) Dosing/purge time units wrong: values are given in seconds from the article (e.g., 0.04 s, 5 s, 4 s, 1 s) but encoded with unit MilliSEC without converting numerics. Convert to milliseconds (e.g., 0.04 s → 40 ms; 5 s → 5000 ms; 4 s → 4000 ms; 1 s → 1000 ms; 0.01 s → 10 ms). (4) NucleationPeriod incorrect: set to 22 cycles (TALD-ZnO on InOx case); for the full-PEALD process nucleation delay is absent; for TALD-ZnO on GaOx it is ~13 cycles. Use the value consistent with the specific process. (5) numberofCycles misused: 12 is the number of supercycles (n=12), not the total ALD cycles. For PE(1/1/1) the total cycles are (3+3+2)*12 = 96. (6) Schema violation: processParameters contains a duplicate filmThickness property outside thicknessControl (not allowed by schema). Remove it; keep thickness only under thicknessControl. (7) Flow rates misassigned: coReactantFlow=150 sccm is not reported for O2; 150 sccm was N2 purging after the O2 plasma step. PurgingGasFlow should reflect 150 sccm after plasma; coReactant (O2) flow is not provided in the article and should not be fabricated. For TALD-ZnO, N2 carrier/purge flows of 60 and 80 sccm are reported; map appropriately. (8) Composition and structure: atomicRatio set to 1:1:1, but XPS after gentle sputtering for PE(1/1/1) is ~1.0/1.0/1.1 (EDX ~1.1/1.0/1.3). Update and cite the method. Crystallinity is not ‘amorphous’ but ‘nearly amorphous, nanocrystalline’ by XRD. (9) Unreported/fabricated properties: optical (n, absorption, band gap), film electrical (resistivity, Hall mobility, carrier density), uniformity, conformality, roughness (AFM), filmDensity (and unit implausible GM-PER-DeciM3), and deviceProperties (TFT metrics) are not provided in the article and should be removed or left unspecified; the study reports MIS J–E data, not TFT performance or Hall measurements. (10) Multiplicity: the paper reports several supercycle compositions (PE(1/1/1), PE(1/1/2), PE(2/1/1), PE(1/2/1)) and one mixed PEALD/TALD sample; the extraction should produce separate process instances for each, not a single mixed process. Correct by: splitting processes per sample; fixing units (pressure, times); correcting numberofCycles; removing duplicate/invalid fields; aligning flow mappings; updating composition and crystallinity; and removing untraceable properties.

completeness.rationale: Very incomplete and partly incorrect. (1) Multiple processes are described in the article but only one process instance is extracted. The paper reports at least five distinct IGZO supercycle recipes: four full-PEALD variants PE(1/1/1), PE(1/1/2), PE(2/1/1), PE(1/2/1) and a mixed PEALD/TALD T(1/1/1). These must be represented as separate processes with their specific subcycle ratios, thicknesses, and outcomes. (2) The aldMethod and reactantSelection improperly merge PEALD and TALD for ZnO into a single process; these belong to different processes. (3) Units and quantities are wrong: dosingTime and purgeTime are specified with unit MilliSEC but numeric values are in seconds (e.g., 0.04 s, 4 s entered as 0.04 and 4.0 ms). Pressure is given with unit MilliM_HG but numeric values are taken from Pa (e.g., 20 Pa not converted to mmHg). (4) numberofCycles=12 is the count of supercycles (n), not the total ALD cycles required by the schema; e.g., PE(1/1/1) should be 12×(3+3+2)=96 cycles. (5) nucleationPeriod=22 cycles corresponds to TALD ZnO on InOx; for the full PEALD process there is no nucleation delay. This is inconsistent and should be process- and sublayer-specific or split into separate processes. (6) Missing reported detail: the special 40 s purge after the last TMGa dose is omitted. (7) Film thickness is fixed at 7 nm, while the article reports 7–9 nm for PEALD samples depending on sequence and ~11 nm for the mixed process; these should be captured per process. (8) Material properties contain fabricated/untraceable values (refractive index, band gap, roughness, density, uniformity, conformality) and deviceProperties (mobility, threshold voltage, etc.) that are not reported; the paper did not fabricate TFTs. (9) FilmComposition atomicRatio is set to 1:1:1, not the measured values from Table 2 (e.g., XPS ~1.0/1.0/1.1 for PE(1/1/1), others differ). (10) Crystallinity is described in the paper as nearly amorphous/nanocrystalline, not purely amorphous. To improve: split into 5 processes with correct subcycle ratios and n, correct all units and totals, align nucleation delays per process, include the 40 s TMGa purge, use reported thicknesses and compositions, and remove unsupported optical/electrical/device metrics.
